    "description": "TORQ Inc. engages in the sale of fastening products in Japan. The company offers various inserts, concrete spacers, PC nuts, coupler and washer, anchor plates, hardware for manhole, stick inserts, flange hardware, connecting plates, and lifting jig; and material handling and transportation equipment, civil engineering and construction equipment, welding/fusing instruments, work/measuring tools, safety and disaster prevention goods, hydraulic equipment, air and electric tools, electrical installation and plumbing fixture, and cutting/grinding tools. It also provides handled products; zinc hat series; anchor birds; new lock anchor; new lock nut; return buckle, multi eye bolt and multi eye bolt hybrid yokobee; round lock bolt/nut; line cap; nord-lock washers; unbrako; bumax; and zennehji marker. The company was formerly known as Kobayashi Metals Limited and changed its name to TORQ Inc. in April 2020. TORQ Inc. was founded in 1926 and is based in Osaka, Japan."
